  == 4. GROUNDING IN ACTUAL USAGE ==

  Every symbol in the vocabulary has been used (implicitly or explicitly)
  across futon missions. This section makes those uses explicit. The logic
  is practical because we have been practising it.

  4.1 и±Ў вЂ” Configuration

  | Context | и±Ў instance | Evidence |
  | Wiring diagram | coordination-exotype.edn | A structured whole: 6 inputs, 6 outputs, 10 components, 30 edges. Referenceable as ":coordination-exotype" without expansion. |
  | Flexiarg pattern | mandatory-psr.flexiarg | A structured whole: conclusion, context, IF/HOWEVER/THEN/BECAUSE. Carryable by pattern-id. |
  | Proof path | gate pipeline output | A structured whole: linked PSRв†’PURв†’PAR chain. Transformable (L1 scans it for tensions). |
  | Session | Claude Code session | A structured whole: context, tools, history. Compresses (compaction) but remains referenceable. |

  4.2 йѓЁ вЂ” Decomposition Regime

  | Context | йѓЁ instance | Evidence |
  | Three-futon split | timescale decomposition | йѓЁ = timescale boundaries (social/task/glacial). Not chosen but perceived (symbolic-individuation). |
  | Gate pipeline | six-gate decomposition | йѓЁ = the six gates G5в†’G0. Binary at each gate (pass/reject), hexadic in composition. |
  | Derivation xenotype | six-step decomposition | йѓЁ = IDENTIFYв†’MAPв†’DERIVEв†’ARGUEв†’VERIFYв†’INSTANTIATE. Sequential, not arbitrary. |
  | Baldwin cycle | triadic decomposition | йѓЁ = NAMINGв†’SELECTIONв†’CANALIZATION. Three phases, not two or four. |

  4.3 е’… вЂ” Articulation

  | Context | е’… instance | Evidence |
  | PSR | pattern selection | The agent makes a decomposition explicit: "I will use this pattern for this task." |
  | ARGUMENT.flexiarg | claim composition | Each S/R/T/C section articulates: makes a claim's structure visible. |
  | Mission scoping | scope in/out | The mission author articulates: what's inside, what's outside. |
  | Git commit | change articulation | The commit message articulates: what changed and why. |

  4.4 й№Ѕ вЂ” Generative Composition (й№µ + зљї)

  | Context | й№µ (potential) | зљї (container) | й№Ѕ (composition) |
  | Gate pipeline | Pattern library (potential approaches) | Gate shapes (Malli schemas) | Validated proof-path (generative: produces evidence) |
  | L1 canonicalizer | Observed tensions (potential patterns) | Library format (flexiarg structure) | New pattern in library (generative: constrains future work) |
  | Social exotype | Agency/realtime patterns (potential requirements) | Wiring diagram format (edn structure) | Validated social-exotype.edn (generative: enables implementation) |
  | Session | Prior knowledge + context | PSR/PUR protocol (recording structure) | Auditable session (generative: feeds glacial loop) |

  4.5 й¦™ вЂ” Embodied Salience

  | Context | й¦™ instance | Evidence |
  | Pattern search | futon3a notions/compass | Signals "this pattern might apply" without proving it. ANN + GloVe similarity, not logical implication. |
  | Hotword matching | patterns-index.tsv hotwords | "deliver" fires on "delivery-receipt" вЂ” salience signal, not identification. |
  | Tension scanning | L1-observe structural-irritation | "This gap-PSR has appeared 3 times" вЂ” cross-layer perception that something recurs, without naming what. |
  | Git archaeology | commit pattern recognition | "These 5 commits all fix forward-declarations" вЂ” perceiving a pattern before it has a name. |

  4.6 е‘і вЂ” Embodied Evaluation

  | Context | е‘і instance | Evidence |
  | PUR | pattern use record | Evaluates by outcome (prediction-error), not by proof. "Did using this pattern help?" is е‘і, not formal verification. |
  | Mana bins | sospeso confidence bins | p в€€ {0.3, 0.6, 0.8, 0.95} вЂ” discrete bins to "reduce self-deception." Evaluation by felt confidence, not computed probability. |
  | ct/mission.clj | 8/8 checks pass | Evaluation by structural test, not semantic proof. The diagram is well-formed; whether it's the right diagram is е‘і. |
  | Code review | Codex review comments | "This could be more defensive" вЂ” evaluative judgement, not provable claim. |

  4.7 рџ”® вЂ” Regulator (иѓЅ + жЌЁ)

  | Context | иѓЅ (capacity) | жЌЁ (setting-down) | рџ”® (regulation) |
  | Sospeso protocol | Confidence p В· C spent on action | (1-p) В· C donated to pool + blast radius note | Proceed at lower confidence with bounded harm |
  | Gate rejection | Pipeline can process the request | Gate rejects with typed error + gate attribution | Fail fast, preserve reversibility |
  | Mission parking | Team could continue the subsystem | :active в†’ :blocked with recorded blocker | Explicit exit over silent abandonment |
  | Context compaction | LLM has N tokens of context | Older context compressed to summary | Continue operating with reduced but sufficient state |

  4.8 жњЄзџҐ / йќћж­»йќћжґ»

  | Context | Instance | Evidence |
