  == 7. AXIOM A7: COMPOSITIONAL SALIENCE ==

  The existing axioms (A1-A5) are operational. A7 is perceptual:

  (A7-precondition
    (if (perceives-й–“ agent interval))
    (then (A7 may proceed: test for й№µ and зљї))
    (else (composition is premature: the interval has not
           been honestly observed)))

  (A7
    (precondition A7-precondition)
    (if (exists (й№Ѕ (вї± й№µ зљї))))
    (and (perceivable й№µ) (perceivable зљї))
    (then (salience emerges))
    (else (generativity remains inert)))

  In operational terms: a pattern library (й№µ) and a recording protocol (зљї)
  may both exist without generating anything вЂ” until an agent perceives that
  they compose under the current decomposition regime (йѓЁ). Salience is the
  moment of that perception. The gate pipeline does not create salience;
  it provides the зљї that makes й№µ's potential actionable. The agent's PSR
  is the е’… that recognizes the composition.

  This axiom explains why Agency/Forum/Drawbridge failed: the components
  existed (й№µ was present) but the recording protocol did not (зљї was absent
  вЂ” no typed evidence shapes, no proof-path store). Without зљї, composition
  could not form. Without composition, salience could not emerge. Without
  salience, the agents could not perceive when their coordination was or was
  not working. The result was йќћж­»йќћжґ»: systems responsive but not self-
  sustaining, eventually abandoned without exit.

  == 8. BOUNDARY RULE: е‘ів†’жњЄ@0 ==

  When evaluation approaches a boundary, it collapses into uncertainty.
  The correct response is containment, not force.

  (rule-card е‘ів†’жњЄ@0
    (when (approach boundary))
    (then
      (collapse (е‘і в†’ жњЄ))
      (bias-toward (ж€’ ењЌ еЊ…)))
    (therefore
      (prefer (small reversible moves))
      (avoid (irreversible commits))))

  Vocabulary for the bias targets:
  - ж€’ (jiГЁ): precept, restraint вЂ” the discipline of not-acting
  - ењЌ (wГ©i): enclosure, surround вЂ” contain the blast radius
  - еЊ… (bДЃo): wrap, contain вЂ” package the uncertainty for later

  This rule governs the transition from the futonic loop's "evaluate"
  phase to the "else" branch. When е‘і (embodied evaluation) reaches the
  edge of what can be evaluated with confidence, the system does not
  push through вЂ” it recognizes it has entered жњЄзџҐ (non-equilibrium)
  and shifts to containment mode.

  Grounding in practice:

  | Context | Boundary | е‘ів†’жњЄ collapse | ж€’/ењЌ/еЊ… response |
  | Sospeso | p drops below 0.95 | Evaluation becomes uncertain | Rescope-to-safety, blast radius note, reversible action only |
  | Gate rejection | G3 can't find pattern | Evaluation of approach is impossible | Typed rejection with gate attribution; don't execute |
  | Mission parking | Subsystem hits blocking failure | Evaluation of progress becomes йќћж­»йќћжґ» | :active в†’ :blocked with recorded blocker; don't abandon silently |
  | L1 canonicalizer | Tension below threshold | Evaluation of pattern candidacy is premature | Record but do not canonicalize; wait for more evidence |
  | Context compaction | Context window approaches limit | Full evaluation of history is no longer possible | Compress to summary; preserve actionable structure, release detail |

  The rule card is the futonic dual of the sospeso protocol. The sospeso
  protocol is operational (confidence bins, mana accounting, blast radius
  notes). The rule card is structural: it says WHEN the transition happens
  (е‘і approaches boundary) and WHAT the bias should be (ж€’/ењЌ/еЊ…), without
  prescribing HOW (that's domain-specific).

  A7 says: composition requires perceiving both й№µ and зљї.
  е‘ів†’жњЄ@0 says: when you can no longer perceive clearly, stop composing
  and start containing. A7 opens the door; е‘ів†’жњЄ@0 knows when to close it.

